  "texts": [
    "First, a one-third octave band analysis 22 is performed by grouping Discrete Fourier transform (DFT) bins into 15 one-third octave bands with the lowest centre frequency set equal to 150 Hz and the highest centre frequency equal to ~4.3 kHz.",
    "Let x(k, m) denote the kth DFT bin of the mth frame of the ground-truth speech.",
    "The norm of the jth one-third octave band, referred to as a time-frequency (TF) unit, is then defined as",
    "where k 1 (j) and k 2 (j) denote the one-third octave band edges rounded to the nearest DFT bin.",
    "The TF representation of the processed speech ŷ is obtained similarly and denoted by Y j (m)."
  ],
